The paper deals with point location in planar subdivisions, which is a classic problem in computational geometry and falls under the category of computational geometry (cs.CG). The use of entropy in the Steiner triangulation suggests that the paper may also be relevant to information theory (cs.IT) and data mining (cs.DM). The data structure presented in the paper involves preprocessing, which is a common technique in data structures (cs.DS). Finally, the paper's focus on query distribution suggests that it may also be relevant to social and information networks (cs.SI).
